    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="666"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d666">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 611.51L9/7</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HMT1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Herrick</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-25">
                        <hi rend="italic">November 25, 1914</hi>.</date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>303. Your 277, November 14, communicated to interested parties. Natural Products
                    Refining Company replies, “Need chrome ore to supply bichromates for reaching
                    [bleaching?], dyeing of cotton, also tanning. Quantity needed, 2,000 tons, so
                    small cannot affect supply for Army Navy purposes.”</p>
                <p>Add National Electrolytic company Niagara Falls, New York, to list in
                    Department’s of October 31.<note n="1" xml:id="d666fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_421">p. 421</ref>.</note>
                    Renew representations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
